cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve paraphrasing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes models to leverage phrase pairs from the PPDB, which involves learning embeddings and improving word embeddings, indicating that it could also fit into the categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its models on similarity tasks, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper introduces new datasets to evaluate short-phrase paraphrasing models, which could also fit into cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
